  FOREIGN KEY (check_id) REFERENCES compliance_checks(id)
)

### STATEMENT

SELECT entity_name, COUNT(*) AS total_reports FROM regulatory_reporting WHERE status = 'Completed' GROUP BY entity_name;

### TABLEDATA

CREATE TABLE compliance_checks (
  id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  check_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
  check_description TEXT,
  created_at TIMESTAMP
)

CREATE TABLE regulatory_reporting (
  report_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
  entity_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
  report_date DATE,
  status VARCHAR(50) DEFAULT 'Pending'
)

CREATE TABLE compliance_history (
  entry_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
  check_id INT,
  result VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
  entry_date TIMESTAMP,
  FOREIGN KEY (check_id) REFERENCES compliance_checks(id)
)

### STATEMENT

SELECT check_name, check_description, result FROM compliance_checks JOIN compliance_history ON compliance_checks.id = compliance_history.check_id WHERE result = 'Failed';
